Under Stalin there was a period when the USSR was actually a "zero party system" because no new members were admitted into the communist party. An actual one party system was only formed later with Khrushchev and Brezhnev. Current American democracy is very similar in that sense.

In the USA you can't join the Republicans or Dems as a party member like normal political parties in other countries. You can "register" as one to vote and you could do volunteer work for them and then later get hired and paid but you don't have membership cards, admissions, etc.
